# Caddy reverse proxy — real domain + automatic Let's Encrypt TLS.
#
# Caddy terminates HTTPS for your domain and forwards everything to the
# edge-proxy, which keeps doing the path routing (Keycloak vs SCIM app) and the
# /demo live-event capture. Caddy automatically sets X-Forwarded-Proto=https,
# so Keycloak (KC_PROXY_HEADERS=xforwarded) issues tokens with the public https
# issuer.
#
# CADDY_DOMAIN is injected from the VM .env (see docker-compose.caddy.yml).
# On first start Caddy obtains a certificate via the HTTP-01 challenge, so the
# domain must resolve to this VM and ports 80 + 443 must be reachable.

{$CADDY_DOMAIN} {
	reverse_proxy edge-proxy:8088
}
